<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1288,2034]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">DIAGNOSIS. This species is easily distinguished by its longer labial palpus, the absence of a costal fold in the male, and the well defined abdominal dorsal pit.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1288,2034]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
DESCRIPTION. MALE. FW length 11.5–12.2 mm (mean = 11.3; n = 7). HEAD: Frons convex, white scaled. Vertex and antenna brownish. Labial palpus with junction of segments II and III an oblique angle, concolorous with head scaling laterally, paler on inner surface. THORAX: Dorsum smooth scaled, brown; tegula concolorous. FW ground color light brown, median fascia darker brown, subterminal fascia, including apex, dark brown; costal fold absent. HW ground color pale brown to cream, except for patch of darker scales at apex; anal area with differentiated long, straight, darker scales. ABDOMEN: Dorsal pit well defined. Genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[259,346,1608,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–70" captionStartId="73.[151,269,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[194,1362,189,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-39@73.[112,1423,148,1857]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 68–70. Male genitalia of Amorbia, valvae spread, aedeagus removed. 68, A. humerosana; 69, A. cuneana; 70, A. santamaria." pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
(slide # EPR08, USNM, 
<collectingCountry box="[663,793,1608,1634]" name="Guatemala" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[808,995,1608,1634]" country="Guatemala" name="Quetzaltenango" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Quetzaltenango</collectingRegion>
, Volcán Santa María; n = 2). Uncus developed. Struts of socii absent. Transtilla pointed anteriorly at middle, uniformly covered with small spines. Valva subrectangular, emarginated. Sacculus well defined, extending beyond margin of valva. Aedeagus 0.75X length of valva, mostly straight, bent at apical 0.25.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1288,2034]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="USNM" country="Guatemala" county="Volcan Santa Maria" location="Ductus" municipality="Lamella" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Quetzaltenango">
FEMALE. FW length 13.0–14.0 mm (mean = 13.5; n = 7). HEAD and THORAX: As described for male. ABDOMEN: Genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[512,601,1808,1834]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–96" captionStartId="82.[151,269,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[260,1345,191,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-37@82.[225,1377,130,1896]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 94–96. Female genitalia of Amorbia. 94, A. humerosana; 95, A. cuneana; 96, A. santamaria." pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
(slide # EPR07, 
<collectionCode box="[822,910,1808,1834]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="Museum">USNM</collectionCode>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[927,1057,1808,1834]" name="Guatemala" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1074,1261,1808,1834]" country="Guatemala" name="Quetzaltenango" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Quetzaltenango</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCounty pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Volcán Santa María</collectingCounty>
; n = 3). 
<collectingMunicipality box="[323,419,1848,1874]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Lamella</collectingMunicipality>
antevaginalis developed into large squarish lateral pockets; median sinus squared, rim of ostium sclerotized. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7464879A1F7BFFF4FF48FB133979DB91:F91260571F7BFFFBFE45F8D33DB3DD21" box="[410,493,1888,1914]" country="Guatemala" county="Volcan Santa Maria" municipality="Lamella" name="Ductus" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" stateProvince="Quetzaltenango">Ductus</location>
seminalis arising near ostium. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7464879A1F7BFFF4FF48FB133979DB91:F91260571F7BFFFBFC87F8D33FF5DD21" box="[856,939,1888,1914]" country="Guatemala" county="Volcan Santa Maria" municipality="Lamella" name="Ductus" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" stateProvince="Quetzaltenango">Ductus</location>
bursae 2.0X length of lamella antevaginalis, nearly uniform in diameter throughout its length
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
